{
  "texts": [
    "While we believe our framework covers the vast majority of biomedical image analysis use cases, suggesting a comprehensive set of metrics for every possible biomedical problem may be out of its scope.",
    "The focus of our framework lies in correcting poor practices related to the selection of common metrics.",
    "However, in some use cases, common reference-based metrics-as a matter of principle -be unsuitable.",
    "In fact, the use of application-specific metrics may be required in some cases.",
    "A prominent example are InS problems in which the matching of reference and predicted instances is infeasible, causing overlap-based localization criteria to fail."
  ]
}